WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:13.000
Music

00:13.000 --> 00:16.000
Excuse me, Officer, can you help me?

00:16.000 --> 00:20.000
Sure. Can you tell me how to get to Linden Street in Riverdale?

00:20.000 --> 00:23.000
Richard Stewart, 46 Linden Street, Riverdale, New York.

00:23.000 --> 00:25.000
You should take the number one subway.

00:25.000 --> 00:27.000
Is there a station near here?

00:27.000 --> 00:29.000
Yes, the station's that way.

00:29.000 --> 00:31.000
Richard, take the number one train to Van Courtland Park.

00:31.000 --> 00:33.000
Number one train to Van Courtland Park.

00:33.000 --> 00:34.000
Thank you.

00:34.000 --> 00:36.000
Anytime, good luck.

00:36.000 --> 00:38.000
Remember the number one train, the uptown platform.

00:38.000 --> 00:40.000
Thank you.

00:40.000 --> 00:57.000
Music

00:57.000 --> 00:59.000
Is this pink too bright for me?

00:59.000 --> 01:01.000
Mm-hmm.

01:01.000 --> 01:03.000
It is a very bright pink.

01:03.000 --> 01:04.000
Yes.

01:04.000 --> 01:10.000
I'm just going to go ahead and see what I'm going to do.

01:10.000 --> 01:13.000
Try this.

01:13.000 --> 01:16.000
It's size eight, but I wear size ten.

01:16.000 --> 01:20.000
How about green?

01:20.000 --> 01:21.000
It's size ten.

01:21.000 --> 01:24.000
Let me try it on.

01:24.000 --> 01:30.000
I'm taking too much of your time.

01:30.000 --> 01:31.000
It's six o'clock.

01:31.000 --> 01:33.000
Where's my husband?

01:33.000 --> 01:35.000
I was expecting him here at 5.45.

01:35.000 --> 01:37.000
Don't worry, the traffic is very heavy at this hour.

01:37.000 --> 01:38.000
I know.

01:38.000 --> 01:42.000
But we're going to be late for dinner.

01:42.000 --> 01:43.000
I'll take this green sweater.

01:43.000 --> 01:45.000
I like the color on me, don't you?

01:45.000 --> 01:50.000
I think it looks terrific on you.

01:50.000 --> 01:53.000
I'm sorry, I'm so late.

01:53.000 --> 01:56.000
I had a really bad day.

01:56.000 --> 01:58.000
It's ten after six.

01:58.000 --> 01:59.000
We're late.

01:59.000 --> 02:01.000
Robby's cooking tonight and dinners at 6.30.

02:01.000 --> 02:02.000
I know.

02:02.000 --> 02:03.000
I know.

02:03.000 --> 02:04.000
I'm really sorry.

02:04.000 --> 02:06.000
I left my bag of film on the ferry.

02:06.000 --> 02:08.000
I went back for it, but the ferry was gone.

02:08.000 --> 02:10.000
I lost a whole day's work.

02:10.000 --> 02:13.000
I'll call the Staten Island Ferry Lost in Found Office.

02:13.000 --> 02:15.000
I didn't think of that.

02:15.000 --> 02:16.000
Thanks.

02:22.000 --> 02:23.000
Hello.

02:23.000 --> 02:24.000
Yes.

02:24.000 --> 02:30.000
The number please of the Staten Island Ferry Lost in Found Office.

02:30.000 --> 02:31.000
5.55.

02:31.000 --> 02:34.000
0.08.

02:34.000 --> 02:35.000
Thank you.

02:35.000 --> 02:40.000
I really appreciate it, Marilyn.

02:40.000 --> 02:42.000
Hello.

02:42.000 --> 02:45.000
Did anyone find a camera bag this afternoon?

02:45.000 --> 02:49.000
A small canvas bag.

02:49.000 --> 02:53.000
On the J.F. Kennedy Ferry.

02:53.000 --> 02:56.000
No.

02:56.000 --> 02:58.000
Maybe someone will find it.

02:58.000 --> 03:00.000
The name is Stewart.

03:00.000 --> 03:01.000
Richard Stewart.

03:01.000 --> 03:08.000
And the telephone number is 555-3090.

03:08.000 --> 03:10.000
Thank you.

03:10.000 --> 03:12.000
Sorry, Richard.

03:12.000 --> 03:14.000
They don't have it.

03:14.000 --> 03:19.000
Thanks anyway.

03:19.000 --> 03:21.000
There was a girl on the ferry.

03:21.000 --> 03:23.000
Tell me about it on the way home.

